月光切割着卧室的灰绒地毯。
她刚沐浴过的湿发贴在我颈侧，
清冷的佛手柑香里混进滚烫的鼻息。
“白天看你演讲时，”
她齿尖不经意擦过我耳骨，
手却探进我睡衣下摆，
“我就在想……这根勒着你的皮带，
该怎么慢慢解开。”

Moonlight cut through the gray velvet carpet in the bedroom.
Her wet hair, fresh from her shower, clung to my neck, the cool scent of bergamot mingled with her hot breath.
“When I watched your speech during the day,”
her teeth brushed against my earlobe,
yet her hand slipped under the hem of my pajamas,
“I was thinking… about how to slowly untie this belt that's constricting you.”
